item.title: Guardian of angels Trust
item.dc:creator: mysticverma
item.content:encoded:
https://anchor.fm/s/2b939740/podcast/rss

Summary

Guardian of Angels Trust is a Registered NGO that takes care of Sick, Injured, Abandonded and Old Animals at their Shelter in Bahadurgarh, Haryana, India. Since 2019, we have rehabilitated and treated more than 3000 street and abandoned Animals & Birds and make a huge impact on the life of these voiceless souls.  We have 24x7 Veterinary & Ambulance Services to make ensure that every animal has got proper treatment. We are running a free OPD for street animals and birds at our shelter. 1 Veterinary Surgeon, 2 Veterinary Para vets and 10 Caretakers are appointed for taking care of these angels. We run a free Anti rabies vaccination drive In Bahadurgarh City.  Apart from these, we provide free On spot treatment facility by our doctors in Bahadurgarh City and nearby 19 villages.  

Facebook Page Link:- https://www.facebook.com/guardianofan...​(Please go through our page once, it will help you have a better understanding about our selfless work towards these voiceless angels and our desperate need of shelter to continue these humanitarian work to help animals in distress. Guardian of Angels Trust has done a wonderful job so far, but now we desperately need your help and support to continue this humanitarian work. 

Please come forward and donate generously to build a shelter. Your contribution can save the lives of hundreds of animals and makes a difference.  Your little contribution can give new life to these thousands of voiceless animals.
